        "Python ownership -> Python carrier for Form-declared choreography",
        "Form-declared choreography -> kernel-router native structure route",
        "repo idea source -> kernel-router native source-index route",
        "repo idea source -> kernel-router native curated portfolio route",
        "graph-node projection proof -> kernel-router native graph-projection route",
        "mutable service calls -> Form-native graph-node mutation carrier",
    ],
    current_gap: "GAP-I1: /api/ideas/router-structure, /api/ideas/source-index, /api/ideas/source-portfolio, and /api/ideas/graph-projection are kernel-first capable; graph-node-port.fk exposes native get/list/count plus create/replace/delete over the storage port, and ideas-graph-projection.fk emits an IdeaPortfolioResponse-shaped read. Public mutable DB-backed /api/ideas routes still enter through FastAPI until method-specific kernel route rows can preserve API-key/contributor-key auth and write the application graph_nodes table directly.",
};

defn ideas_router_reading() = {
    observed: [
        "api/app/routers/ideas.py carries the live HTTP routes",
        "services carry persistence and computation",
        "tests prove selected route contracts and this Form expression",
    ],
    inferred: [
        "ideas.py is not one function; it is a portfolio organism with ten route recipe families",
        "the north star is closure through evidence, relation, value flow, and contribution",
    ],
    measured: [
        "api/tests/test_ideas_router_form.py",
        "python3 scripts/validate_spec_quality.py --file specs/ideas-router-form-expression.md",
    ],
    mystery: [
        "which recipe family wants to become kernel-front-door first remains a later body reading",
    ],
};

defn example_ideas_router_structure() = ideas_router_structure();
